  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The formation and destruction of closed loops in a system of strings is discussed. Coupled equations are set up to describe the evolution of the system and it is shown that it must either evolve to a scaling solution where the persistence length is proportional to time or to a situation where the strings come to dominate the energy density. The first case provides a very attractive cosmological scenario in which the loops generate the density fluctuation needed for galaxy formation.</subfield>
